Design lineage: this crate's wire-protocol structure (method names, JSON
shapes, status-hash construction, merkle-proof encoding, ScriptHashStatus
state machine) follows romanz/electrs (https://github.com/romanz/electrs),
which is the reference implementation of an Electrum protocol server in
Rust. The Electrum protocol itself is open and documented at
https://electrumx.readthedocs.io/en/latest/protocol.html.

Code in this crate is original implementation written from spec, not a
literal vendoring of electrs sources. We track electrs's choices closely
where wire compatibility requires it (status hash construction; merkle
encoding; method dispatch shape) and diverge where our own subscription
infrastructure (`node_index::SubscriptionRegistry`) renders electrs's
internal state machine unnecessary.

The romanz/electrs project is MIT-licensed; the upstream LICENSE text
follows for reference and for compliance with its attribution norms.

